# links
https://github.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh
http://code.joejag.com/2014/why-zsh.html
http://mikebuss.com/2014/02/02/a-beautiful-productive-terminal-experience/

# features
- better tab completion (files, directories, switches, env vars)
- shared command history
- useful aliases (git, macports, rsync, yum)
- alert on failed commands
- globbing
- spelling correction
- vibrant plugin community

# recursively show all text files
ls **/*.txt

# recursively show all files > 100 MB
ls -lh **/*(Lm+100)
